                    <input type="checkbox" class="read-more-state" id="post-1" />
                    <div class="read-more-wrap">
                        <p>By default, search queries are only temporarily saved during the current session. If you want to use certain search queries more than once, you can save them in your account.</p>
                        <div class="read-more-target">
                            <p>To save a search query, first select the menu item “Search History” located on the right-hand side below the label "My Account".</p>
                            
                            <a class="thumbnail" href="#" data-image-id="" data-toggle="modal" data-title="" data-caption="" data-image="/themes/ixtheo2/images/content_img/en/save_searches_eng.png" data-target="#image-gallery">
                                <img class="img-responsive" src="/themes/ixtheo2/images/content_img/en/save_searches_eng.png" alt="<?=$this->transEscAttr('symbolic_image_table59');?>.">
                            </a>

                            <p>You will then see under "Current searches" a list of all the searches you performed so far in the current session. You can permanently save any search query in that list by clicking on the "Save" button to the right of the search query. It is then moved above to the list of “Saved searches”, where it remains permanently available and can be executed again by clicking on it.</p>
                            <p>In this way, you can quickly get an overview of newly published literature on a specific topic in which you have an enduring interest. This is especially useful for complex queries.</p>
                        </div>
